evaporate /ɪˈvæpəˌreɪt/

(evaporating,evaporated,evaporates) 

1. V-T/V-I When a liquid evaporates , or is evaporated , it changes from a liquid state to a gas, because its temperature has increased. 使…蒸发; 蒸发 

例： Moisture is drawn to the surface of the fabric so that it evaporates. 湿气被吸到织物表面而蒸发。 

例： The water is evaporated by the sun. 水被太阳照射而蒸发。 

2. evaporation N-UNCOUNT 蒸发 

例： The soothing, cooling effect is caused by the evaporation of the sweat on the skin. 凉爽怡人的效果是由皮肤上汗液挥发所致。 

3. V-I If a feeling, plan, or activity evaporates , it gradually becomes weaker and eventually disappears completely. (情绪、计划、活动) 逐渐消逝 

例： My anger evaporated and I wanted to cry. 我的怒气渐渐消了，就想哭了。

